Galton

Francis Galton was a famous statistician born in 1822. You can read all about him hear on Wikipedia.

galton-pic

Father Son Height Data

Here is some famous data from Galton that we can easily load into R using the UsingR library. This is helpful for practicing making plots, or doing other statistical techniques.

library(UsingR)
data(father.son)
head(father.son)
##    fheight  sheight
## 1 65.04851 59.77827
## 2 63.25094 63.21404
## 3 64.95532 63.34242
## 4 65.75250 62.79238
## 5 61.13723 64.28113
## 6 63.02254 64.24221

So does a fathers height help predict the sons height? Ive made this plot to help you assess this claim.

plot(father.son$fheight, father.son$sheight)
